First time we tried this place.
The food was fine.
Not particularly memorable, but not bad.
I like Genghis Grill better, but this place is cheaper.
And the quantity of food is reasonably generous.
Menu seemed to have a variety of choices.
I quickly narrowed in on the yakisoba.
The teenager went for a teriyaki bowl of some sort.
Both came with rice, and we had enough left over for another meal later.
I wouldn't make a point of coming here, but if I were in the area I could see stopping in for an (relatively) inexpensive bite.

If you're a lover of katsu or teriyaki chicken/beef, this is a great fast-food restaurant.
The food is cooked after you place your order.
The grill right behind the counter so you can see you food being cooked immediately.
Portion size is fairly large and they have a nice selection of lunch combos.
I love that they have the sauces on the condiment bar so you don't have to ask for more sauce!
Parking can be difficult since it's part of the Tempe Marketplace, but not a huge deal.

Great place to go if you don't want to wait for a table at the other food spots.

