This place hit the spot with a simple white meat (add 99 cents) chicken veggie teriyaki bowl to go.
The small was pretty big for $7, so that was enough.
Chicken was freshly cooked and some good sized veggies including the usual suspects (carrots, cabbage and broccoli) were present.
Some weird signs all over regarding misuse of to-go sauce were kind of freaky.
You can't get self service sauce to go and they charge 25 cents for more sauce.
This is kind of lame because the two cups they gave me ran out before I was done.
Are you really going to run out of freakin sauce if somebody grabs two extra tiny cups?
This policy was lame.
Shame on all the sauce abusers in Phoenix and Yogi for being so damn cheap and petty.

